title:	feat(compare): add --include flag to filter resource type
state:	OPEN
author:	haimn-support
labels:	
assignees:	
reviewers:	
projects:	
milestone:	
number:	13
url:	https://github.com/port-experimental/port-cli/pull/13
additions:	166
deletions:	39
auto-merge:	disabled
--
## Summary

- Wires up the pre-existing (but no-op) `--include` flag on `port compare` so it actually filters which resource types are fetched and diffed
- Omitting `--include` preserves the original behaviour — all resource types are compared
- Invalid resource names return a clear error message at the CLI layer

## Changes

- **`fetcher.go`** — added `IncludeResources` to `FetchOptions`; passed it to the export collector so only requested resources are fetched from live orgs
- **`compare.go`** — forwarded `opts.IncludeResources` into both source and target `FetchOptions` and into `Diff()`
- **`differ.go`** — updated `Diff()` to accept `include []string`; added `shouldInclude()` helper; each of the 7 resource types is now guarded by it
- **`commands/compare.go`** — added validation of resource names against the allowed set
- **`differ_test.go`** — fixed existing call sites; added `TestDiffer_Diff_IncludeFilter_PagesOnly`, `TestDiffer_Diff_IncludeFilter_EmptyMeansAll`, `TestShouldInclude`
- **`README.md`** — documented `--include` usage with examples

## Test plan

- [ ] `go test ./...` passes locally
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org>` (no flag) compares all resource types as before
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org> --include pages` compares only pages
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org> --include pages,blueprints` compares both
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org> --include invalid` returns a clear error
- [ ] Works with export file inputs (`--source ./file.tar.gz`)

---
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index e1ff979..496fadf 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -225,8 +225,10 @@ find backups/ -name "port-backup-*.tar.gz" -mtime +30 -delete

 ### Compare Organizations

+By default, `port compare` compares **all** resource types (blueprints, actions, scorecards, pages, integrations, teams, users). Use `--include` to narrow the comparison to specific types.
+
 ```bash
-# Compare two configured organizations
+# Compare two configured organizations (all resource types)
 port compare --source staging --target production

 # Compare with verbose output (show identifiers)
@@ -235,9 +237,18 @@ port compare --source staging --target production --verbose
 # Compare with full field-level diff
 port compare --source staging --target production --full

+# Compare only pages
+port compare --source staging --target production --include pages
+
+# Compare pages and blueprints together
+port compare --source staging --target production --include pages,blueprints
+
 # Compare export files
 port compare --source ./staging-backup.tar.gz --target ./prod-backup.tar.gz

+# Compare only pages between export files
+port compare --source ./staging-backup.tar.gz --target ./prod-backup.tar.gz --include pages
+
 # Output as JSON (for scripting)
 port compare --source staging --target production --output json

@@ -246,8 +257,13 @@ port compare --source staging --target production --output html --html-file repo

 # CI/CD mode: exit code 1 if differences found
 port compare --source staging --target production --fail-on-diff
+
+# CI/CD mode scoped to pages only
+port compare --source staging --target production --include pages --fail-on-diff
 ```

+Valid `--include` values: `blueprints`, `actions`, `scorecards`, `pages`, `integrations`, `teams`, `users`.
+
 ### Pre-Production Testing

 ```bash
diff --git a/internal/commands/compare.go b/internal/commands/compare.go
index b7f97f2..69fbb24 100644
--- a/internal/commands/compare.go
+++ b/internal/commands/compare.go
@@ -82,13 +82,22 @@ Examples:
 				targetOrg = target
 			}

-			// Parse include list
+			// Parse and validate include list
 			var includeList []string
 			if include != "" {
 				includeList = strings.Split(include, ",")
 				for i := range includeList {
 					includeList[i] = strings.TrimSpace(includeList[i])
 				}
+				validResources := map[string]bool{
+					"blueprints": true, "actions": true, "scorecards": true,
+					"pages": true, "integrations": true, "teams": true, "users": true,
+				}
+				for _, r := range includeList {
+					if !validResources[r] {
+						return fmt.Errorf("invalid resource: %s. Valid resources: blueprints, actions, scorecards, pages, integrations, teams, users", r)
+					}
+				}
 			}

 			opts := compare.Options{
diff --git a/internal/modules/compare/compare.go b/internal/modules/compare/compare.go
index bfcbec0..8cabcba 100644
--- a/internal/modules/compare/compare.go
+++ b/internal/modules/compare/compare.go
@@ -29,10 +29,11 @@ func (m *Module) Execute(ctx context.Context, opts Options) (*CompareResult, err

 	// Fetch source data
 	sourceOpts := FetchOptions{
-		OrgName:      opts.SourceOrg,
-		FilePath:     opts.SourceFile,
-		ClientID:     opts.SourceClientID,
-		ClientSecret: opts.SourceSecret,
+		OrgName:          opts.SourceOrg,
+		FilePath:         opts.SourceFile,
