--
## Summary

- Wires up the pre-existing (but no-op) `--include` flag on `port compare` so it actually filters which resource types are fetched and diffed
- Omitting `--include` preserves the original behaviour — all resource types are compared
- Invalid resource names return a clear error message at the CLI layer

## Changes

- **`fetcher.go`** — added `IncludeResources` to `FetchOptions`; passed it to the export collector so only requested resources are fetched from live orgs
- **`compare.go`** — forwarded `opts.IncludeResources` into both source and target `FetchOptions` and into `Diff()`
- **`differ.go`** — updated `Diff()` to accept `include []string`; added `shouldInclude()` helper; each of the 7 resource types is now guarded by it
- **`commands/compare.go`** — added validation of resource names against the allowed set
- **`differ_test.go`** — fixed existing call sites; added `TestDiffer_Diff_IncludeFilter_PagesOnly`, `TestDiffer_Diff_IncludeFilter_EmptyMeansAll`, `TestShouldInclude`
- **`README.md`** — documented `--include` usage with examples

## Test plan

- [ ] `go test ./...` passes locally
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org>` (no flag) compares all resource types as before
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org> --include pages` compares only pages
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org> --include pages,blueprints` compares both
- [ ] `port compare --source <org> --target <org> --include invalid` returns a clear error
- [ ] Works with export file inputs (`--source ./file.tar.gz`)

